// Perfect Number

A perfect number is a positive integer that is equal to the sum
of its positive divisors, excluding the number itself. A diviso
r of an integer x is an integer that can divide x evenly.

Given an integer n, return true if n is a perfect number, otherwise
return false.*/

class Solution {
public:
    bool checkPerfectNumber(int num) {
        if(num == 1) return false;
        int sum = 1;
        for(int i = 2; i * i <= num; i++) {
            if(num % i == 0) {
                sum += i;

                if(i != num / i)
                    sum += num / i;
            }
        }
        return sum == num;
    }
};
